research_municipality_step.notes: The elected officials for Tatum City, TX, include the Mayor and five Council Members, also referred to as Aldermen. Michael Henry serves as the Mayor. Tate Smith holds the roles of Mayor Pro-Tem and Council Member for Place 3. J.R. Smith is a Council Member for Place 1, Wendell Moore for Place 2, and Robin Palmer for Place 4. Greggory Cole is listed as a Council Member in recent documents. While a specific 'Place' number for him was not explicitly found in the most recent sources, he is assumed to hold 'Place 5' to complete the five council member positions, based on the structure of the Tatum City Council.
